## 🔧 Customization

### Change Colors
Open `style.css` and edit the `:root` variables at the top:

```css
:root {
  --navy:       #0d1b3e;   /* Primary dark color */
  --gold:       #c9a84c;   /* Accent / highlight color */
  --cream:      #fafaf7;   /* Form body background */
  --border:     #d0d8e8;   /* Input border color */
}
```

### Change Fonts
Replace the Google Fonts `@import` line at the top of `style.css`:

```css
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=YourFont&display=swap');
```

### Add/Remove Form Fields
Each field follows this pattern in `index.html`:

```html
<div class="field">
  <label for="fieldId">Field Label</label>
  <input id="fieldId" name="fieldId" type="text"
         placeholder="Hint text" title="Field Label">
</div>
```

